          "createdAt": "2026-03-10T17:42:45Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-03-10T17:42:45Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 42,
              "body": "Supporting URI templates definitely makes sense :) I wasn't entirely sure yet how to best model them, but I suppose we can have more discussion based on concrete examples.\r\n\r\nFor now, I introduced a separate quality named `sdfVariables` for defining the schema of URI variables, but maybe we can also merge it with `sdfParamters`.",
              "createdAt": "2026-03-10T17:42:45Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-03-10T17:42:45Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDORZnW6c7p6pZT",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "2b82dd7"
          },
          "author": "rohitmohan96",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "",
          "createdAt": "2026-03-10T18:16:35Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-03-10T18:16:35Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 4,
              "body": "Can you use the `property-protocol-map` defined in sdf-protocol-map \u00a73.1.1 here?",
              "createdAt": "2026-03-10T18:16:35Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-03-10T18:16:35Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDORZnW6c7p6z_z",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "2b82dd7"
          },
          "author": "JKRhb",
          "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "",
          "createdAt": "2026-03-10T18:23:25Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-03-10T18:23:25Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 4,
              "body": "Good point, that would simplify this definition.\n\nThis reminds me, though, that `read` and `write` have different default methods, which should probably also be reflected in the CDDL schema. Can we also cover that using the `property-protocol-map`? Or do we need to introduce different definitions for that anyway?",
              "createdAt": "2026-03-10T18:23:25Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-03-10T18:24:33Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDORZnW6c7p84V0",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "2b82dd7"
          },
          "author": "rohitmohan96",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "",
          "createdAt": "2026-03-10T19:57:47Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-03-10T19:57:47Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 4,
              "body": "Oh that is a good point. \nThe text says:\n>  To extend $$SDF-PROPERTY-PROTOCOL-MAP for a new protocol (e.g., \"new-\n   protocol\"), implementors MUST use the property-protocol-map generic\n   with the protocol name and a map type defining the protocol-specific\n   attributes.\n\nIt shouldn't be a MUST if it doesn't allow for having two different mappings for read and write. \nLet me see how to rework that CDDL in the sdf-protocol-mapping draft. ",
              "createdAt": "2026-03-10T19:57:47Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-03-10T20:00:41Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDORZnW6c7p9BTH",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "2b82dd7"
          },
          "author": "rohitmohan96",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "",
          "createdAt": "2026-03-10T20:04:28Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-03-10T20:04:28Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 4,
              "body": "Although, in this case, wouldn't it just be `property-protocol-map<\"coap\", coap-vocabulary>`?",
              "createdAt": "2026-03-10T20:04:28Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-03-10T20:04:28Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
